1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,720
CHAPTER ONE

2
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:20,400
A child arrives

3
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:26,360
1989, Smallville, Kansas, USA.

4
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:29,520
Suddenly the sky was dark.

5
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:32,760
There were hundreds of meteors in the sky.

6
00:00:32,760 --> 00:00:36,480
They went faster and faster.

7
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:41,360
There was a very small spaceship in the centre of the meteors.


8
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:44,840
There was one person in this spaceship.

9
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:47,680
A child.

10
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:50,240
Nothing happened in Smallville.

11
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:56,120
It was a small town in Kansas and it was a very boring place.


12
00:00:56,120 --> 00:01:01,640
Then, one day, everything changed.

13
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:06,280
Lionel Luthor arrived from Metropolis in his helicopter.

14
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:10,600
He was a rich man, but he was not a nice man.

15
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:14,120
He loved money, not people.

16
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:17,600
His young son Lex sat next to him.

17
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:20,160
Lex was nine years old.

18
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:23,480
He had red hair and blue eyes.

19
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:27,360
His face was white and his eyes were closed.

20
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:30,120
He was very frightened.

21
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:32,960
'Lex!' shouted his father.

22
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:35,520
'Open your eyes now!'

23
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:38,240
'I can't,' Lex said.'

24
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:41,160
I hate this helicopter.'

25
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:45,640
'Luthors aren't frightened of anything,' Lionel said.

26
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:50,120
'Look out of the window - now!'

27
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:54,000
Lex slowly opened his eyes and looked down.

28
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,320
I'm going to die, he thought.

29
00:01:56,320 --> 00:02:02,960
Two men waited for the helicopter in the car park of an old factory.


30
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:08,160
The men were brothers: Dale and Bill Ross.

31
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:14,160
'Why does Lionel Luthor want to buy our factory?' asked Dale.


32
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:19,280
'I don't know,' said Bill, 'but we need his money.

33
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,640
He isn't going to change anything.

34
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:26,720
He told us that, and I believe him.'

35
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:32,560
Jonathan Kent and his wife Martha went into a shop on Main Street.


36
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:36,360
Their faces were brown from the sun and their jeans were old.


37
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:39,840
They lived on a farm.

38
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:43,360
'Afternoon, Nell,' Jonathan said.

39
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,960
'Hello, Jonathan,' Nell said.

40
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,600
She smiled at him.

41
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,920
She liked Jonathan.

42
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:52,920
'Hello, Martha,' she said.

43
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,120
She didn't smile at Martha.

44
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:57,400
She didn't like her.

45
00:02:57,400 --> 00:03:01,520
'I'd like some tulips,' said Martha.

46
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:05,120
'Red tulips, please.'

47
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,640
There was a little girl in the shop.

48
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:10,160
She was very pretty with dark hair.

49
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:13,200
She was three years old.

50
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:16,640
'Hello, Lana,' said Martha.

51
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:19,840
'Where are your mom and dad today?'

52
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:23,480
'They're at the homecoming game,' Nell said.

53
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:24,520
'Here are your tulips.'

54
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:28,640
She gave them to Jonathan.

55
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:36,960
In the street, Martha said sadly, 'Oh Jonathan, I looked at Lana's
little face and I...'

56
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,800
She stopped.

57
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:42,040
'I know, Martha,' said Jonathan.

58
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:45,400
'We both want a child.'

59
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:49,560
The meteors came closer and closer.

60
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,920
At the factory, Lex was bored.

61
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:57,720
He walked away into a cornfield next to the factory.

62
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,560
Lionel Luthor read the papers.

63
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:05,440
'Where do I put my name?' he asked the Ross brothers.

64
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,120
He smiled.

65
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:10,040
The factory was his now.

66
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:14,560
Alone in the field, Lex suddenly heard something.

67
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,480
'Help me!'

68
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:18,240
What was it?

69
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,120
Then he heard it again.

70
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:23,400
'Help me!'

71
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:29,080
He walked through the corn and suddenly there was a scarecrow.


72
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,200
Lex was frightened.

73
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:33,960
That scarecrow can talk! he thought.

74
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:37,680
But then it wasn't a scarecrow.

75
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,920
It was a teenage boy.

76
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:42,320
The boy was on a big wooden pole.

77
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:45,240
He had no shirt.

78
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:49,640
There was a big red S on the front of his body.

79
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:54,800
'Help me, please,' he said one more time.

80
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,400
THOOOMMM!!!

81
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:59,880
The first big meteor crashed into the cornfield.

82
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:04,200
Lex ran.

83
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:07,120
A car stopped opposite Nell's shop on Main Street.

84
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:13,200
Nell took little Lana in her arms and walked out of the shop.


85
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,840
Lewis and Laura Lang were in the car.

86
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:16,840
Lana saw them.

87
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:20,200
'Mommy! Daddy!' she shouted.

88
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:25,080
Nell looked up and saw a big meteor in the sky.

89
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:27,280
THOOOMMM!!!

90
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:31,400
The meteor crashed into the Langs' car.

91
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:34,920
Lana's parents were dead.

92
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:40,520
Lionel Luthor ran across the cornfield. 'Lex!

93
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:42,880
Where are you?' he shouted.

94
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:45,840
He saw some red hair on the ground.

95
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:48,400
Then he found his son.

96
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,760
Lex was on the ground.

97
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,760
He was very frightened.

98
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:55,800
But where was his beautiful red hair?

99
00:05:55,800 --> 00:06:00,720
He was nine years old and he now had no hair at all.

100
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:06,160
Jonathan and Martha Kent were on their way home.

101
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:09,720
Suddenly a meteor hit the road behind them.

102
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:13,800
'What was that, Jonathan?' asked Martha.

103
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,320
'What's happening?'

104
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:17,360
THOOOMMM!!!

105
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:21,120
A spaceship crashed into the road in front of them.

106
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:25,960
Jonathan tried to stop the car but it crashed into a cornfield.


107
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:30,320
When they opened their eyes, they saw a boy.

108
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:34,800
He was about three years old and he had no clothes.

109
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:38,560
The boy pulled Jonathan's car door.

110
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,840
It opened.

111
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:43,280
Then he pulled Martha's car door.

112
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:44,200
It opened too.

113
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:48,040
Martha and Jonathan were very surprised.

114
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:50,640
They were soon out of the car.

115
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:53,440
Martha took the boy in her arms.

116
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:56,880
'Are you okay?' asked Jonathan.

117
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:59,320
'Yes, I'm fine.

118
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:01,560
You?' said Martha.

119
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,360
'Yes.

120
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:07,480
Children don't fall from the sky,' Jonathan said.

121
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:12,040
'Then where did he come from?' Martha asked.

122
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:15,720
'I don't think his mom and dad are from Kansas!'

123
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:19,440
'We can't keep him, Martha,' said Jonathan.

124
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:21,640
'What can we say to people?

125
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:24,280
"We found him in a cornfield!"?'

126
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:29,360
'We didn't find him, Jonathan,' said Martha.

127
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:31,840
'He found us.'

128
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:40,760
CHAPTER TWO

129
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:49,120
Special and different

130
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:54,080
Jonathan and Martha took the boy home to their farm.

131
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:56,120
They named him Clark.

132
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:59,520
They didn't tell him about his arrival.

133
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:02,040
They didn't tell other people either.

134
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:07,440
If someone asked, they said, 'He's Martha's sister's son.

135
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:08,680
She died.'

136
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:13,240
They didn't want Clark to be different from other children.

137
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,080
But he was different.

138
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,560
He was special.

139
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:18,840
He was very strong.

140
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,680
He was very fast.

141
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:22,640
Nothing hurt him.

142
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:27,360
When he was eight, a big milk can hit his head.

143
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,280
It didn't hurt him.

144
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:35,720
2001, Smallville, Kansas, USA.

145
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:38,840
Clark sat at his computer.

146
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,880
Every morning he used the Internet.

147
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:48,720
He wanted to find stories about special people - very strong
people, very fast people.

148
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:51,000
'Clark Kent!'

149
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,160
Martha called.

150
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:54,720
'You're going to be late for the bus!'

151
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:58,680
'OK, I'm coming,' shouted Clark.

152
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:05,200
He put on his school clothes and shoes, cleaned his room and
put his schoolbooks in his bag.

153
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:07,080
All in one minute!

154
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:11,040
Martha came into his room with some clothes.

155
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:15,840
'You can wear these to the homecoming dance this weekend,' she
said.

156
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:19,320
'I'm not going, Mom,' said Clark.

157
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:21,840
'I haven't got a girl to go with.'

158
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:25,280
'Did you ask anyone?' Martha asked.

159
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,520
'No,' he said.

160
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:29,480
He ran down to the kitchen.

161
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:33,640
'What's that letter, son?' asked Jonathan.

162
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:37,160
'It's for the football team,' said Clark.

163
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:39,320
'They want some new players.'

164
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:42,880
'You can't do it,' said Jonathan.

165
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:46,160
'Oh, please, Dad,' said Clark.

166
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:48,200
'I can run slowly.

167
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,760
I can be careful.'

168
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:55,280
'I'm sorry, Clark,' said Jonathan, 'but the answer is no.'

169
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:59,360
'I don't want to be different,' shouted Clark.

170
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,880
'I can never do normal things.

171
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:04,400
People at school think I'm a loser.'

172
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:06,320
He ran out of the door.

173
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:11,720
'We must tell him about the spaceship,' Martha said to Jonathan.


174
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:15,320
Clark walked to the bus stop.

175
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:16,880
He was late again.

176
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:19,520
The school bus drove off without him.

177
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:22,240
'Oh, no!' he said.

178
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:26,240
'Everything's going wrong today.'

179
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,320
Suddenly he smiled a big smile.

180
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:33,720
He turned and ran through the fields at 100 kilometres an hour.


181
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:37,160
The bus arrived at school.

182
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:41,400
Clark's friends, Pete Ross and Chloe Sullivan, were on it.

183
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:44,320
Chloe was new in Smallville.

184
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,800
Her dad worked at LuthorCorp.

185
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:51,320
She wrote for the school newspaper and took photos for it.

186
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:54,040
She was always ready with her camera.

187
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:59,480
'Are you going to the dance with anyone?' Pete asked Chloe.

188
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:02,920
'No, not yet,' said Chloe.

189
00:11:02,920 --> 00:11:06,520
'Well, if Clark doesn't ask you...'

190
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:10,560
'I'm not interested in Clark, Pete,' she said.

191
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:13,440
'Right,' said Pete.

192
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,480
He knew that wasn't true.

193
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:20,640
'Well, we can go to the dance together if you want,' he said.


194
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:23,080
'Not boy and girl.

195
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,240
Friend and friend.'

196
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:27,200
Suddenly Clark was there.

197
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,720
'Hi, you two,' he said.

198
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:33,960
Pete and Chloe were very surprised to see their friend.

199
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:37,320
'We saw you at your farm,' Chloe said.

200
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,240
'You weren't on the bus!'

201
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,920
'I came a different way,' said Clark.

202
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:47,240
'Are you ready for the football team, Clark?' asked Pete.

203
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:50,800
'I'm not going to do it,' said Clark.

204
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:55,800
'But, Clark,' said Pete, 'do you want to be the scarecrow?'

205
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:59,480
'The scarecrow!' Chloe said loudly.

206
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,360
'What's the scarecrow?'

207
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,680
'Shh!' said Pete.

208
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:06,520
'This happens here every year, Chloe.

209
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:10,960
Before the homecoming game, the football players choose someone.


210
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:12,560
A loser.

211
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:17,000
They take him to the cornfield and take all his clothes.

212
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,600
Then they write a big red S on the front of his body.'

213
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:24,760
'And they put him on a big wooden pole,' said Clark.

214
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:27,120
'So he's a scarecrow.'

215
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:30,120
'How terrible!' said Chloe.

216
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:36,800
Then Clark saw a beautiful girl with long, brown hair and a lovely
smile.

217
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:40,400
'See you later,' he said to his friends.

218
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:44,440
Clark walked across to Lana Lang.

219
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,480
He was a metre from her.

220
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:49,200
Suddenly he crashed to the ground.

221
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,120
His books went everywhere.

222
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:55,400
Why does this always happen near Lana? he thought.

223
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,400
Is it because I like her?

224
00:12:57,400 --> 00:13:02,040
'Hi, Clark, are you okay?' she asked.

225
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:04,280
'Hi, Lana,' he said.

226
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:06,160
'Yeah, I'm fine.'

227
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,560
She gave his books to him.

228
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,960
'You're reading Nietzsche, huh?

229
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,320
Are you man or superman?'

230
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:16,640
'I don't know,' Clark said.

231
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:18,120
They smiled.

232
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:24,400
'Lana!' shouted Whitney Fordman, a tall, good-looking student.


233
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:26,440
He was Lana's boyfriend.

234
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:29,640
Whitney was fantastic at sports.

235
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:31,880
He was in all the school teams.

236
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:34,440
He ran up and kissed Lana.

237
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:45,720
They walked away together.

238
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:51,200
CHAPTER THREE

239
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,520
Two terrible shocks

240
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:58,280
A student looked at the photos of the school sports teams.

241
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:01,520
He looked at the 1989 photo.

242
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:06,920
'You're late for your class, young man,' said a teacher behind
him.

243
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,680
The student turned.

244
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:11,800
'What's your name?' asked the teacher.

245
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:13,200
'Are you new?'

246
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:17,520
Suddenly the student hit the teacher in the face.

247
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:23,360
A big blue electric shock went from the student's hand into the
teacher's body.

248
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:26,080
The teacher crashed into the wall.

249
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:32,040
The student took the photo of the three happy football players
and left the school.

250
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:35,600
I'm gonna get you! he thought.

251
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:42,760
Lex Luthor drove his Porsche through the country to the LuthorCorp
factory in Smallville.

252
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:49,320
'The Smallville factory doesn't make any money,' Lionel Luthor
said to his son.

253
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:51,080
'Go to Smallville.

254
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,520
Make changes!'

255
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:55,240
So Lex left Metropolis.

256
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,800
And here he was.

257
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,640
In the centre of nowhere.

258
00:14:58,640 --> 00:14:59,800
Great!

259
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:03,280
Lex arrived at LuthorCorp.

260
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:07,680
He was twenty-one years old and he still had no hair.

261
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:10,640
He walked into the factory.

262
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:13,960
A man sat at a desk with his lunch.

263
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:18,280
'Mr Luthor!' the man said, surprised.

264
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,320
'My name's Gabe Sullivan.'

265
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:22,200
'Call me Lex.''

266
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:26,360
The workers aren't happy, Lex,' said Gabe.

267
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,920
'They're frightened about their jobs.'

268
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:31,600
'It's OK,' said Lex.

269
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,720
'I want everyone to stay.'

270
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:36,760
'But your father said...'

271
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:40,560
'I'm not my father,' said Lex Luthor.

272
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:47,920
Later, Lex drove down a small country road at 100 kilometres
an hour.

273
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:50,600
His car radio played loud music.

274
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:54,840
Not far away, Clark was on a bridge.

275
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,880
He looked into the water.

276
00:15:56,880 --> 00:16:00,600
He thought about his life and he wasn't happy.

277
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,640
He didn't hear Lex Luthor's car.

278
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:07,400
Lex answered his mobile phone.

279
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,760
He didn't look at the road for a minute.

280
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,600
He drove onto the bridge.

281
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:14,080
Then he saw Clark.

282
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:18,680
He tried to stop the car but Clark was right in front of him.


283
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:21,680
I'm going to hit him! Lex thought.

284
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:23,680
Their eyes met.

285
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:26,920
Then Lex's car crashed into Clark.

286
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,360
THOOOMMMH!

287
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:33,200
The car and Clark went over the bridge and into the water.

288
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:37,800
Clark's eyes closed and everything went black.

289
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:52,320
CHAPTER FOUR

290
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,440
The green necklace

291
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:59,240
Under the water, Clark opened his eyes.

292
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:00,960
He was OK.

293
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,640
He wasn't hurt.

294
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:05,280
Then he remembered the car.

295
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:06,720
THE CAR!

296
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:09,840
He found the car with Lex in it.

297
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:12,200
Lex's eyes were closed.

298
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:15,880
Clark pulled open the door and pulled Lex out.

299
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:19,240
He took him in his arms and started to swim.

300
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:24,200
When Clark put Lex on the ground, he thought he was dead.

301
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,800
Clark put his left hand on Lex's body.

302
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,920
