303
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:36,320
'One, two. One, two. One, two.

304
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:37,520
Come on!

305
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:38,520
Don't die!

306
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:39,280
' he said.

307
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:42,760
Some water came out of Lex's mouth.

308
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:45,880
He opened his eyes and saw Clark.

309
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:48,120
He was very surprised.

310
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:51,840
'But I hit you!' he said.

311
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:55,520
'Well, I'm not dead,' said Clark.

312
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:58,760
Clark looked at the bridge.

313
00:17:58,760 --> 00:18:03,360
A car hit me at 100 kilometres an hour.

314
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:05,000
I'm not hurt.

315
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,400
I am not normal, he thought.

316
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:12,880
The police and a doctor arrived.

317
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:15,520
Then Jonathan Kent arrived too.

318
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:19,320
Jonathan put his arms around Clark.

319
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:22,400
'Are you OK, son?' he asked.

320
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:25,280
'I'm fine, Dad,' said Clark.

321
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:27,840
'I'm Jonathan Kent.

322
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:31,480
This is my son,' Jonathan told a policeman.

323
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:34,480
'Who was the stupid driver of the car?'

324
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:37,680
'I was,' said Lex Luthor.

325
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:42,000
'You have a very special son, Mr Kent,' he said.

326
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,360
'You saved my life, Clark.

327
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:46,120
How can I thank you?'

328
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:49,680
'Drive more slowly,' said Jonathan.

329
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:56,080
After dinner that night, Clark went up to his special room in
the barn.

330
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:58,480
He looked at the night sky.

331
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:02,640
Then he looked over at the farmhouse next to the Kents' farm.


332
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:07,280
The front door opened and Lana Lang came out.

333
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:09,120
Clark smiled.

334
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:11,680
But then Whitney came out.

335
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:15,440
Whitney put his arms around Lana.

336
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:18,800
'Are you alone tonight?' he asked.

337
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:23,120
'Yes, Aunt Nell's at Lex Luthor's,' said Lana.

338
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:26,120
'Did you hear about Clark?' she said.

339
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:28,560
'He saved Lex's life today.'

340
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:31,400
'Clark?' Whitney said.

341
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,000
'Clark Kent?'

342
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,400
'Yes,' said Lana.

343
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:38,320
'Sometimes people can surprise you.'

344
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:41,480
Whitney didn't want to talk about Clark.

345
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:43,480
He wanted to talk about Whitney.

346
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:47,240
'I've got a game on Saturday,' he said.

347
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:49,960
'Some important people are going to be there.'

348
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:52,600
'That's great!' Lana said.

349
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:55,840
Whitney wanted to be a top football player.

350
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:57,240
It was his dream.

351
00:19:57,240 --> 00:20:00,280
She gave her green necklace to him.

352
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:03,120
The necklace was part of a meteor.

353
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:04,800
A special meteor.

354
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:08,560
This meteor hit Lana's parents' car.

355
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:12,800
'I can't take this, Lana,' Whitney said.

356
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:14,880
'It means everything to you.'

357
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:18,280
'Keep it just for the game,' she said.

358
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:22,080
He put it in his jacket.

359
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:30,720
Then he kissed her.

360
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:36,800
CHAPTER FIVE

361
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,560
The true story

362
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:42,680
Tony Carozza had a job at a car place.

363
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,080
It was evening.

364
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:46,400
It was almost time to go home.

365
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:48,960
A boy came into the shop.

366
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:51,520
'I'm sorry,' said Tony.

367
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,640
'Were closed.'

368
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,760
The boy said nothing.

369
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:57,120
Tony looked at him carefully.

370
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:59,920
'I know you,' he said.

371
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:02,760
'You were that scarecrow years ago!

372
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:04,480
What happened to you?

373
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:06,640
Why aren't you older?'

374
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:09,640
The boy still said nothing.

375
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:12,640
'Answer me, Stupid!' said Tony.

376
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,120
'I'm talking to you!'

377
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:17,840
The boy suddenly hit Tony in the face.

378
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:23,400
A big blue electric shock went from his hand into Tony Carozza's
body.

379
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:26,080
Tony crashed onto the floor.

380
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:27,720
He didn't move.

381
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:33,120
On the wall, there was a photo of three happy football players.


382
00:21:33,120 --> 00:21:36,600
The boy smiled and left the shop.

383
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:40,040
It was the day after the car crash.

384
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:45,440
When Clark walked into school, every student said, 'Nice work,
Clark!'

385
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:49,640
'Am I at the right school?' Clark asked Pete and Chloe.

386
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:53,520
'You saved Lex Luthor's life,' said Chloe.

387
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:56,320
'This is going in the school newspaper.'

388
00:21:56,320 --> 00:22:00,600
'My dad hates the Luthors,' said Pete.

389
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:05,400
'Yes, but Lionel Luthor bought your dad's factory.

390
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:07,760
Not Lex,' said Clark.

391
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:15,800
When Clark arrived home on the farm that afternoon, he found
a new red car in front of the house.

392
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:18,120
There was a letter on the car.

393
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:19,920
Clark opened it.

394
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:23,040
Thank you, Clark, he read.

395
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:25,240
I hope you like red.

396
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,840
Clark looked at the car.

397
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:29,800
He was very excited.

398
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:33,600
'You can't keep it, Clark,' Jonathan said.

399
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:35,160
'Why not?'

400
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:38,320
'Because the Luthors aren't good people.

401
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:40,720
They're rich thanks to Smallville.

402
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:44,080
They bought our friends' houses and their farms.'

403
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:47,760
'Lex's father did all that,' said Clark.

404
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:49,160
'Not Lex.'

405
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:52,640
'I'm sorry, Clark,' Jonathan said.

406
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:54,200
'I know you're angry.'

407
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:57,040
'Angry!' shouted Clark.

408
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,880
'You have no idea!'

409
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:01,720
He ran up to his room in the barn.

410
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:06,240
'You must tell him now,' Martha said.

411
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:09,480
Jonathan went to Clark's room.

412
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:12,160
He put his arms around his son.

413
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:18,000
'I'm going to tell you the story of the day of the meteors,'
he said.

414
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,320
He gave Clark a picture.

415
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:23,160
There were lots of letters and numbers on it.

416
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:24,920
Was it a language?

417
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:29,760
'I think this is from your mom and dad,' he said.

418
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:33,680
'What does it say?' Clark asked.

419
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:37,160
'I have no idea,' said Jonathan.

420
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:39,720
'They came from a different world.'

421
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:43,920
'A different world?!' laughed Clark.

422
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:46,160
'So I arrived in a spaceship?

423
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,800
That's stupid!'

424
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:52,080
'Do you want to see that spaceship?' asked Jonathan.

425
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:53,800
'It's under the barn.'

426
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:59,240
When he saw the little spaceship, Clark was very angry.

427
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:03,120
'Why didn't you tell me this before?' he shouted.

428
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:04,960
He ran out of the barn.

429
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:13,520
CHAPTER SIX

430
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:21,560
A quick kiss

431
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:34,960
Lana Lang looked at the words: Lewis Lang 1957-1989 Laura Lang
1959-1989.

