00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:05,760
'Not very well,' said Lana.

445
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:07,760
'They died when I was three.

446
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:09,920
Do you want to meet them?'

447
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:12,720
She sat on the ground.

448
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:17,920
'Mom, Dad, this is Clark Kent,' she said.

449
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:21,520
'Hi, Mr and Mrs Lang,' said Clark.

450
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,800
'I'm sorry?

451
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:24,880
What's that?'

452
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:27,400
He sat down and listened.

453
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:36,880
'Your mom says, "You're never alone, Lana,"' he said, 'and your
dad says, "You're beautiful."'

454
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:39,280
Lana smiled.

455
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:42,200
'Thank you, Clark,' she said.

456
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:45,800
'Can I walk home with you?' asked Clark.

457
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,200
'Yes.

458
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:48,760
Thanks,' said Lana.

459
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:55,800
When they arrived at Lana's house, she said, 'We talked for a
long time tonight, Clark.

460
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:57,360
It was nice.'

461
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:59,520
She kissed him quickly.

462
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:01,280
'Good night, Clark.'

463
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:03,360
She ran into the house.

464
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:06,240
Clark was very happy.

465
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:09,360
But there was someone at Lana's house.

466
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:13,320
He saw the kiss and he was very angry.

467
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:15,680
It was Whitney Fordman.

468
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:22,360
The next day before school, Clark drove the red car back to Lex
Luthor's house.

469
00:26:22,360 --> 00:26:24,880
The house was big and old.

470
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:26,760
The front door was open.

471
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:28,400
Clark walked in.

472
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:30,880
'Hello!' he shouted.

473
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,760
'Is anyone at home?'

474
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:35,920
'Clark,' said Lex.

475
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:37,560
'What are you doing here?

476
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:39,200
How's your new car?'

477
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:42,720
'I love it,' said Clark.

478
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:44,760
'But I can't keep it.'

479
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:46,520
'Why not?

480
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:49,000
You saved my life, Clark.

481
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:52,240
I want to thank you,' Lex said.

482
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:55,880
Then he said, 'Oh, I get it.

483
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:57,720
Your dad doesn't like me.'

484
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,920
Clark didn't say anything.

485
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:03,880
'It's OK,' said Lex, 'I understand.'

486
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:07,120
'It's not you,' said Clark.

487
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:09,320
'He doesn't like your father.

488
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:11,800
Thank you for the car, Lex.

489
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,840
I'm sorry I can't keep it.'

490
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:17,600
'I changed after that crash,' said Lex.

491
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:20,080
'When I was under the water...

492
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:23,680
I saw my life in Smallville in a new way.

493
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:32,080
I can see now... this isn't the end of my old life in Metropolis...
it's the start of my new life here.

494
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:37,280
So, thank you, Clark.

495
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:46,800
I hope we can be friends for a long time.'

496
