Clark looked at the two photos of Jeremy Creek.

530
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:46,120
'Jeremy had a big electric shock twelve years ago,' said Chloe.


531
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:49,320
'He was in hospital for twelve years.

532
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:53,080
A few days ago he woke up and ran away.'

533
00:29:53,080 --> 00:29:57,840
'So why is he back in Smallville?' asked Clark.

534
00:29:57,840 --> 00:30:01,000
'Why is he giving electric shocks to people?'

535
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:07,200
'Because twelve years ago,' Pete said, 'they put him on a pole
in a field.

536
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:09,480
He was that year's scarecrow!'

537
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:14,600
'The meteors crashed into Smallville that day!' said Chloe.

538
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:17,680
Oh no! thought Clark.

539
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:20,320
All this happened because of me!

540
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:22,920
That was the day of my arrival.

541
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:27,560
He looked at a photo in one of the old newspapers.

542
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:29,160
It was a little girl.

543
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,960
She had a terrible look on her face.

544
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:37,280
It said under the photo, Meteor hits mom and dad.

545
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:41,800
'So what do you think, Clark?' asked Chloe.

546
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:46,960
Clark knew that little face in the photo.

547
00:30:46,960 --> 00:30:48,880
'Oh no! Lana!'

548
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:53,400
'Why didn't you tell me about this before?' he shouted.

549
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:55,080
'I did this!'

550
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:57,280
He ran from the room.

551
00:30:57,280 --> 00:31:01,160
In front of the school, he met Whitney.

552
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:03,760
'Hi, Clark,' said Whitney.

553
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,400
'I'm looking for you.

554
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:07,680
You're this year's scarecrow!'

555
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:12,720
'Leave me alone, Whitney,' said Clark angrily, 'or I'm going
to...'

556
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:15,520
'You're going to what?' said Whitney.

557
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:17,080
'Come on, Clark.

558
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:17,960
Hit me!'

559
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,720
He took off his jacket.

560
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:24,640
Clark moved nearer to Whitney but he suddenly started to fall.


561
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:29,400
He saw Lana's green necklace under Whitney's open T-shirt.

562
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:32,960
'What's between you and Lana?' shouted Whitney.

563
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:35,160
'You can have her necklace!'

564
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:38,800
He took off the necklace and put it on Clark.

565
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:40,840
'But you can't have Lana!

566
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:43,280
I'm taking her to the dance tonight.'

567
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:45,720
Clark didn't feel well.

568
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:47,440
He tried to move.

569
00:31:47,440 --> 00:31:49,600
And then everything went black.

570
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:53,120
Whitney and two of his friends put him in a car.

571
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:56,440
Jeremy Creek watched everything.

572
00:31:56,440 --> 00:32:08,640
And he remembered this day, twelve years ago.

573
00:32:08,640 --> 00:32:14,440
CHAPTER EIGHT

574
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:16,880
A big red S

575
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:19,880
Clark woke up.

576
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:22,760
He was in a cornfield, on a pole.

577
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:24,680
He was very cold.

578
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:27,480
It was night and it was October.

579
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,080
He looked down.

580
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:32,720
There was a big red S on the front of his body.

581
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:35,200
He tried to move his arms.

582
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:37,000
I can't move.

583
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,520
What's wrong with me? he thought.

584
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:41,480
It's the necklace!

585
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:45,560
Suddenly there was a boy in front of him.

586
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:48,800
'It hurts,' said the boy.

587
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,520
'I remember that.'

588
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:53,880
'You're Jeremy Creek,' said Clark.

589
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:55,400
'No.

590
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:59,480
Jeremy Creek died twelve years ago,' said the boy.

591
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:01,720
He started to walk away.

592
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:05,120
'Where are you going?' asked Clark.

593
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:08,120
'To the school dance,' said Jeremy.

594
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:10,960
'I didn't go in 1989.'

595
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:14,040
'Please help me,' said Clark.

596
00:33:14,040 --> 00:33:16,520
'No,' Jeremy said.

597
00:33:16,520 --> 00:33:18,320
'You stay here.

598
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:20,560
I don't want to hurt you.'

599
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:23,840
Jeremy walked down the road.

600
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:26,640
Lex Luthor drove by and saw him.

601
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:29,920
'I know that boy,' he thought.

602
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:31,120
'But how?

603
00:33:31,120 --> 00:33:32,320
From where?'

604
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:34,560
He stopped the car.

605
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:37,720
Then he remembered the field twelve years ago.

606
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:39,200
The boy on the pole.

607
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:40,120
The big red S.

608
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:44,600
He got out of the car and went into the field.

609
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:47,360
'Help me,' he heard.

610
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:49,320
'Help me, please.'

611
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:52,400
It's not possible, Lex thought.

612
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:54,160
Then he saw him.

613
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:56,200
'Clark!' he shouted.

614
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:58,520
Lex helped Clark.

615
00:33:58,520 --> 00:34:00,760
Clark pulled off the necklace.

616
00:34:00,760 --> 00:34:04,040
'You need a doctor, Clark,' Lex said.

617
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:08,600
Without the necklace, Clark was suddenly Clark again.

618
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:10,720
He didn't need a doctor.

619
00:34:10,720 --> 00:34:12,440
'I'm OK.

620
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:14,760
Thanks, Lex,' he said.

621
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:18,040
He found his clothes and ran into the night.

622
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:21,080
Lex saw the necklace on the ground.

623
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:25,080
He put it in his jacket and walked back to his car.

624
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:30,600
At the school dance, the band played and everyone danced.

625
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:33,280
Jeremy Creek didn't dance.

626
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:35,680
He was behind the school building.

627
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:38,920
He opened the door of a large box.

628
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:41,080
WATER, it said.

629
00:34:41,080 --> 00:34:44,600
They're all going to die now, he thought.

630
00:34:44,600 --> 00:34:47,400
Suddenly Clark was behind him.

631
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:50,480
'Stop this now, Jeremy,' he said.

632
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,880
'You!' said Jeremy.

633
00:34:52,880 --> 00:34:54,720
'What are you doing here?'

634
00:34:54,720 --> 00:34:58,280
'You're not going to hurt my friends,' said Clark.

635
00:34:58,280 --> 00:35:01,440
'You don't understand,' said Jeremy.

636
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:04,400
'I'm doing this for you and the others.

637
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,720
No more scarecrows!'

638
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:08,080
'No, Jeremy.

639
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:10,040
Stop it,' said Clark.

640
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:14,360
Jeremy hit Clark in the face but he had a surprise.

641
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:16,360
Clark wasn't hurt.

642
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:19,480
There was a car next to Jeremy.

643
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:21,800
He opened the door and started it.

644
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,400
He drove at Clark.

645
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:28,000
Clark put his arms in front of him, but Jeremy didn't stop.

646
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:31,960
Clark was on the front of the car when it hit the Water box.

647
00:35:31,960 --> 00:35:34,240
There was water everywhere.

648
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:37,360
It gave Jeremy a big electric shock.

649
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:39,040
His body was blue.

650
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:41,400
Then everything was quiet.

651
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:44,360
Clark pulled the car door.

652
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:45,360
It opened.

653
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:48,200
'Are you OK?' he asked.

654
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:51,240
'Who are you?' asked Jeremy.

655
00:35:51,240 --> 00:35:53,160
'I want to go home.'

656
00:35:53,160 --> 00:35:57,200
Clark watched the end of the homecoming dance.

657
00:35:57,200 --> 00:36:00,480
Lana and Whitney danced in the centre of the room.

658
00:36:00,480 --> 00:36:02,320
Then they kissed.

659
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,040
A long kiss.

660
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:06,120
Clark was sad.

661
00:36:06,120 --> 00:36:08,080
He turned and left.

662
00:36:08,080 --> 00:36:12,360
There were three cars in a line in the car park.

663
00:36:12,360 --> 00:36:17,040
That's Whitney's car and his friends' cars, Clark thought.

664
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:18,920
He had an idea.

665
00:36:18,920 --> 00:36:23,160
He took one car and put it on top of another one.

666
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:27,680
Then he took the third car and put it on top of the other two.


667
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:29,000
He waited.

668
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:33,800
When students came out and saw the cars, they laughed.

669
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:38,000
Then Whitney came out, with his arm around Lana.

670
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,640
He saw his car.

671
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:43,800
'Who did this to my car?' he shouted angrily.

672
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:47,080
Everyone laughed and Lana smiled.

673
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:48,240
EPILOGUE

674
00:36:48,240 --> 00:37:03,520
'Thanks for the dance'

675
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:08,120
'Clark,' called Jonathan when he came home.

676
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:09,760
'Lex was here.

677
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,240
This is for you.'

678
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:15,040
He gave Clark a small box and a letter.

679
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:18,120
Lana's necklace was in the box.

680
00:37:18,120 --> 00:37:19,960
Clark read the letter.

681
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:24,000
I found this necklace in the cornfield, Clark.

682
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:27,880
We are friends now, so please keep this box.

683
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:31,000
My mother gave it to me many years ago.

684
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,840
It's very special.

685
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,160
Lex.

686
00:37:34,160 --> 00:37:37,800
Clark opened the box and saw the necklace.

687
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:42,040
He didn't feel well.

688
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:46,080
He closed the box again, and he was OK.

689
00:37:46,080 --> 00:37:48,520
It was a special box.

690
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:51,920
'I must remember that,' he thought.

691
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:54,480
'Hello, Clark.'

692
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:55,800
It was Lana.

693
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:57,280
In his room in the barn.

694
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:59,840
'Lana!' he said, surprised.

695
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:01,600
'What are you doing here?'

696
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:05,000
'You didn't come to the dance,' she said.

697
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:08,240
She walked up to him and put her arms around him.

698
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:10,400
'Let's dance now.'

699
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:13,240
They danced to the music.

700
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:15,560
Clark closed his eyes.

701
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:17,960
Suddenly he heard a car.

702
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:19,640
He opened his eyes.

703
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:21,520
Lana wasn't there.

704
00:38:21,520 --> 00:38:23,720
It was a daydream.

705
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:26,520
He looked through the window.

706
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:29,040
A car arrived at Lana's house.

707
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,960
'The necklace!'

708
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:33,680
Clark took it to Lana's house.

709
00:38:33,680 --> 00:38:35,800
He put it on her front door.

710
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:39,720
He was back in his room before Lana opened the car door.

711
00:38:39,720 --> 00:38:43,560
He moved faster than the wind and nobody saw him.

712
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:48,440
When Lana arrived at her front door, she saw the necklace.

713
00:38:48,440 --> 00:38:50,720
She took it and put it on.

714
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:55,480
Oh Whitney, you are fantastic, she thought.

715
00:38:55,480 --> 00:39:10,320
'Good night, Lana,' Clark said quietly.

716
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:16,428
'Thanks for the dance.'
